data.value: You can capture screen by clicking File-Capture Screen. Neutrino Screen Capture will capture screen without its own window. If you want to capture screen with its window you can use Area Capture. If Neutrino Screen Capture is in maximized state it will capture background screen. You should resize Neutrino Screen Capture before capturing a new screen. But if you don't , it woun't create any problem. In that case , just make sure the background screen is your desired screen. You could press Ctrl+Shift+S for capturing screen. Using Area Capture you can capture a area , just you will have to select the area. You can also use timer for capturing screen. Click Tools-Timer Capture or press Ctrl+Shift+T , write down a specific time and press Set Time. During progressing time Neutrino Screen Capture will hide itself and capture screen after that time. Every time when Neutrino Screen Capture capture screen or an area , it shows notification in the taskbar. You also will be able to convert image. Click Tools-Convert Image. Open your image. Select your desired format from combo box and press convert.
